1 (b) A person authorized to access privately owned critical
2 infrastructure or a key facility operating an unmanned aircraft or
3 unmanned vehicle for the purpose of inspecting, maintaining,
4 repairing, constructing, or otherwise working on that critical
5 infrastructure or key facility.
6 (c) A person operating an unmanned aircraft or unmanned
7 vehicle over or on critical infrastructure or a key facility with
8 the consent of the owner or operator of the critical infrastructure
9 or key facility.
10 (8) (5) As used in this section:
11 (a) "Critical infrastructure" means that term as defined in
12 section 2 of the cyber civilian corps act, 2017 PA 132, MCL 18.222.
13 (b) (a) "Key facility" means that term as defined in section
14 552c.
15 (c) (b) "Unmanned aircraft" means that term as defined in
16 section 3 of the unmanned aircraft systems act, 2016 PA 436, MCL
17 259.303.
18 (d) "Unmanned vehicle" means a water- or land-based vehicle
19 that is piloted remotely, or autonomously through use of an on-
20 board computer, communication links, and any additional equipment
21 that is necessary for the vehicle to operate safely.
